        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 3:02PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 302 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Centenary, or 13 miles north of Buckingham, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
New Canton...
Gold Hill...
and Centenary.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
